						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Lazycow wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">edit: wait, it's a 16k +8k rom... can't I use a 32k +8k rom without bankswitching?!</div><br />Yes, <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/NROM" class="postlink">NROM (&quot;mapper 0&quot;)</a> supports that.  Just make sure you pad things correctly with your assembler and/or linker so that your vectors/etc. end up in the last 16KByte portion of the 32KBytes (I'm sure you know why).</div>

